Zain Saudi 4G Services to Cover Kingdom By End 2012, COO Says

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-09-14T13:48:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-14/zain-saudi-4g-services-to-cover-kingdom-by-end-2012-coo-says.html
Zain  Saudi Arabia , a unit of Mobile
Telecommunications Co. of Kuwait, said its fourth-generation
wireless service will cover all of Saudi Arabia by the end of
2012.  Zain Saudi started today the high-speed mobile Internet
network service in the three main cities of Riyadh, Jeddah and
Dammam, Ahmed Alfaifi, chief operating officer, said at a news
conference in Riyadh today.  Alfaifi said he expects the service to help increase
existing customers’ data usage and may attract new subscribers.
The technology allows customers to use enterprise applications,
online gaming and high-definition video streaming. Saudi Arabia
had 11.4 million  Internet users  at the end of 2010, according to
a report by the country’s  Communications and Information
Technology Commission .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in  Riyadh  at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
